    "summary": "Summary\nGerrie has successfully assisted global and mid-sized organisations in addressing regulatory enforcement, cross border reputation and forensic distress matters. Gerrie's drive is to get a positive result. \n\nGerrie leads Forensic at Deloitte North South Europe llp and is part of Deloitte Forensic's global exco. \n\nProfile\nGerrie heads Deloitte's Forensic & Financial Crime offering at Deloitte North South Europe. In this integrated offering clients seek the support of Deloitte on Crisis, Forensic, and Compliance matters. \n\nGerrie has previously been leading Forensic teams and Fraud & Compliance Risk Management Services in various roles at big4 organisations. \n\nGerrie has a wide range of Forensic expertise covering various jurisdictions and industries with over twenty-five years of combined forensic, governance, audit and accounting experience. Gerrie is a Registered Accountant with the Royal NIVRA. Gerrie gathered his knowledge and expertise while working in the audit and advisory practices of Deloitte and KPMG. \n\nGerrie has a pragmatic and result driven approach by focusing on the facts, will hit the ground running and is known for his capability to effectively manage large and complex assignments. He brings local and cultural working experience from working with and leading global teams and gains respect and appreciation for his speedy and accurate response to delicate matters. \n\nFor several years, Gerrie worked in Australia and the Asia region leading the fraud risk management services of KPMG. He introduced and expanded forensic accounting skills into the audit practices. Following this international experience, he returned back Europe in 2007 managing Forensic Investigation and Dispute practices in the Netherlands.",
